raw_data.name: Ebony Experience Gallery
raw_data.full_address: 7714 Matthews-Mint Hill Rd, Mint Hill, NC 28227
raw_data.subtypes: Art gallery, Art museum, Book store, Coffee shop, Event venue, Tea house, Tea store, Winery

reviews_data.review_text: Hosted our daughter’s tea themed birthday party and everything was perfect! From the tea sandwiches to the doughnuts my daughter requested to have, they made this experience beautiful and fun for the kids all at the same time. I love how beautiful the space is and how it was just perfect for the tea birthday party. I would definitely recommend! And if you are just looking for a nice chill out spot for a cup of tea and a good book, this is your place too!

Omg i fell in love with this place! Great books, soooo cute, and anesthetically pleasing, they even have coffee and wine ! Me and my friend enjoyed this place and will definitely be back for the events
I met the owner. We had a wonderful experience . The wine is excellent. I purchased two bottles . It ‘s more than a winery . Please go and check it out . The owner is wonderful!!!
I absolutely love this place the owner Camillya is awesome!! 10/10 I do recommend.

I am soo in love with this black owned, women owned establishment. Camillya is very engaged and navigated the entire experience. She also has some of the best wine. 🍷 I loved the book selection as well.
Black. Pretty. Books. Camillya (the owner). The place to visit. 10/10 Recommend
This place was most definitely a vibe. Camillya, the owner, made the experience top tier. The wine experience and book selection was great

I came to check out my cousin’s new place and I sat in a place of pride and excitement for her! She has created a peaceful, calming, educational, classy, dainty atmosphere. I sat with my latte and delicious dessert and soaked up the rich conversation and quiet time to read my book from her expansive bookstore. This is a must-come, must-see, must-experience. Looking forward to coming back!
Wonderful service. Camellia's service is amazing, hands down. I come to the Ebony Bloom Tea Lounge and Bookstore for the experience and enjoy it every time. Highly recommend!
Beautiful space! Really enjoyed my time here.
This was a great experience, Camille was so gracious and welcoming. This would be an amazing solo trip or great for a group adventure.
Camille was so very gracious  to us when we came to visit . This is a great place to visit the team room was incredible, will definitely come back again

I had a lovely time in there! The atmosphere was relaxing and the owner was sociable. I got a frappe for a drink and she wanted it to be to my exact liking. So, I definitely appreciate the ✨️✨️✨️✨️effort ✨️✨️✨️✨️she displayed to make it custom for me. The different experience set ups are so beautiful. I learned some facts  from the gallery experience that I can take back and teach to my scholars. :) Thank you💌
Amazing experience!!!
Me and my husband enjoyed the experience. Will be back soon!!
Great staff. Super dope spot for my tea drinkers, wine drinkers, book lovers. I will definitely be back!
This is definitely an amazing experience! The decor is simply stunning. Camilla is an absolute joy to be around. I will absolutely be back!
Such an amazing experience! The tea was wonderful, Camilla provided a great experience. I can’t wait to come back!

Found this spot nearby, popped in and was not disappointed. Arrived soon after opening to find a hidden gem. Enjoyed the full experience by browsing the bookstore, enjoying the most delicious iced coffee in the tea room, and finally the All Eyes on Congo art exhibit. Can’t wait to go back.
Everything was amazing great vibes amazing drink

Oh my goodness!!! This space is outstanding! Such a hidden gem in plain sight. Bookstore, tea gallery and event space all in one. I have never experienced anything like it. Please come check this out!!!
This is a very nice venue for an intimate gathering.
This place is fantastic!!! Movie night, book readings, Black owned, and featuring her very own Wine & Spirits.
Loved the experience at Ebony. I can't wait until the next event.
Very dense space packed with history, art, and culture. Warm environment that feels welcoming to anyone. The coffee is great too.

Love this place. It’s so beautiful and full of culture. The owner is very knowledgeable and kind. There are literally 3 different sections in one spot you’ll find yourself there for hours, especially in the tea room and book store.
The decor in the tea lounge is amazing and the book store has a great selection of books from black authors and their prices are unbeatable!!!!
This joint is awesome 10/10. I will be back

This venue is beautiful.  Filled with all sorts of art. The space is perfect to just enjoy solo or date night.  Loved the various styles represented. Saw a few fav artists whose works I already own.  Excited to return.
I didn't try the wine this evening but heard it was delicious.  I enjoyed sorting the vendors as well.

The space is not hard to locate but be mindful GPS may drop you in the front of the building.  Be sure to drive down to the back where there is plenty of additional parking.  Easy access.
